<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="6e985883-035a-4116-a3d0-d26a01f499f9" >

    <h2><a name="goods"></a>Goods and professional services</h2> 
<p>Goods are tangible products while professional services are provided by individuals or firms with the necessary professional licenses, certifications or training to contribute to defined and approved projects at the university. As they tend to include hands-on roles, professional services are distinct from consulting work as the latter provides strategic advice used for decision-making.</p> 
<p>Some examples of professional service providers include chartered accountants, engineers, medical doctors, lawyers, architects and some specializations from IT professionals.</p> 
<p>For help differentiating between professional and consulting services, please contact&nbsp;<a href="/content/ryerson/financial-services/contact/purchasing-payment.html">Purchasing Services</a>.</p> 
